navigation-api.article3_body:
The core entry point is window.navigation. Key usage scenarios:

1. Intercepting navigation (core of SPA routing)
Listen to the navigate event to handle all navigation in one place. event.intercept() lets you define what to load:

```js
navigation.addEventListener('navigate', (event) => {
  event.intercept({
    async handler() {
      const content = await loadPage(url.pathname);
      render(content);
    }
  });
});
```

2. Programmatic navigation

```js
navigation.navigate('/new-page', { state: { foo: 'bar' } });
navigation.traverseTo(key);  // by key, not index
navigation.back();
navigation.forward();
```

Each method returns { committed, finished } — two Promises for precise lifecycle tracking.

3. State management

```js
navigation.navigate(url, { state: { scrollPos: 200 } });
navigation.updateCurrentEntry({ state: { sidebarOpen: true } });
const state = navigation.currentEntry.getState();
```

getState() returns a structured clone, not the same reference like history.state.

4. History inspection

```js
navigation.entries() // each entry has url, key, index
entry.addEventListener('dispose', () => { /* cleanup */ });
```
